To clone this project:
1. Clone the repo.
2. Create a virtual environment.
3. Activate it.
4. Install the project dependencies from pyproject.toml.

Typical commands on macOS/Linux:
    git clone <repo-url>
    cd r2pythonds
    python3 -m venv .venv
    source .venv/bin/activate
    python -m pip install --upgrade pip
    python -m pip install -e .

Typical Windows PowerShell terminal:
    git clone <repo-url>
    cd r2pythonds
    py -m venv .venv
    .venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
    python -m pip install --upgrade pip
    python -m pip install -e .

Typical Windows Command Prompt terminal:
    git clone <repo-url>
    cd r2pythonds
    py -m venv .venv
    .venv\Scripts\activate.bat
    python -m pip install --upgrade pip
    python -m pip install -e .